  <graph id="G" edgedefault="undirected">
    <node id="n0">
      <data key="v_content">0: Marie Curie was a Polish-born physicist and chemist. She was born in Warsaw, Poland in 1867. Curie moved to Paris to study at the Sorbonne University. She conducted research on radioactivity and discovered the elements polonium and radium.

Marie Curie married Pierre Curie, a French physicist. Together they won the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1903. She later won a second Nobel Prize in Chemistry in 1911. Their daughter Irene Joliot-Curie also became a famous scientist.</data>
      <data key="v_name">passage-1d46af80df40c74a5b67f8e497a45aac</data>
    </node>
    <node id="n1">
      <data key="v_content">1: Albert Einstein was a theoretical physicist who developed the theory of relativity. He was born in Ulm, Germany in 1879. Einstein worked at Princeton University in New Jersey. He won the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1921. His famous equation is E=mc^2.

Einstein collaborated with other scientists including Niels Bohr and Max Planck. He befriended Charlie Chaplin, who invited Einstein to the premiere of his film City Lights.</data>
      <data key="v_name">passage-c36456e926a2b0dc8ae9ae37c2b1bf7f</data>
    </node>
    <edge source="n0" target="n1">
      <data key="e_weight">1</data>
    </edge>
  </graph>
